                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 1.0,
                  "response": "That’s correct!"
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Many argue that self-fulfillment is essential to one’s happiness; however, it is not the basis of human culture. Without language we could not pass culture from one generation to the next. LO 2.2 Know the components of symbolic culture: gestures, language, values, norms, sanctions, folkways, mores, and taboos; also explain the Sapir-Whorf hypothesis."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: While culture is a key component of a society, society refers to the group of people who share that culture and territory. Without language we could not pass culture from one generation to the next. LO 2.2 Know the components of symbolic culture: gestures, language, values, norms, sanctions, folkways, mores, and taboos; also explain the Sapir-Whorf hypothesis."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Competition is an important element of a capitalist economic system, not the basis of human culture. Without language we could not pass culture from one generation to the next. LO 2.2 Know the components of symbolic culture: gestures, language, values, norms, sanctions, folkways, mores, and taboos; also explain the Sapir-Whorf hypothesis."
                }
              }
